-- European Stocks Climb as Banks Seek Lower Level of ECB Loans Than Forecast
-- Andrew Rummer
-- 2010-06-30T12:19:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/european-stocks-erase-gain-as-u-s-companies-add-fewer-jobs-than-estimated.html

          
          
             European stocks erased their advance
after a report from ADP Employer Services showed U.S. companies
added fewer jobs than forecast in June.  
 The Stoxx Europe 600 Index slipped 0.2 percent to 243.29 as
of 1:18 p.m. in London, having earlier risen as much as 0.7
percent.  
          
          


  


        